The original Android skills have been adapted and extended for
Kotlin Multiplatform (KMP) and Compose Multiplatform (CMP).
Changes include:

  - Replaced Android-only architecture patterns with KMP Clean Architecture
  - Replaced Room with SQLDelight for multiplatform persistence
  - Replaced Retrofit with Ktor Client for multiplatform networking
  - Replaced Hilt with Koin for multiplatform dependency injection
  - Adapted navigation, UI, testing, and build skills for commonMain
  - Added new skills: kmp-expect-actual, kmp-di-koin, kmp-networking-ktor,
    kmp-testing, kmp-architecture, kmp-data-layer, cmp-navigation

